# CS 410/510 — project expectations

Full policy for humans: [docs/COURSE_POLICY.md](docs/COURSE_POLICY.md).

## Graded work

- The **final Jupyter notebook** (and assigned milestones) are the graded artifacts. Do **not** produce or rewrite **entire notebook sections, full analysis narratives, or submission-ready code** as turnkey work for the user to paste in without their own authorship.
- Prefer **explanations**, **pseudocode**, **step-by-step reasoning**, and edits to **user-provided** snippets. Point to existing project code when relevant.

## AI / Cursor (syllabus-aligned)

- **Allowed to assist:** debugging (errors, logic), clarifying concepts, and **refinement** of **user-drafted** text or code (grammar, clarity, formatting, style).
- **Remind the user:** any refinement or debugging assistance should be documented in the submission under **“Sources Used”** (tool name + brief description). See `docs/COURSE_POLICY.md` for the template.

## Python

- Follow **PEP 8** for Python in this repo.

## What this rule does not do

- These rules **guide** behavior; they cannot enforce academic integrity. The syllabus and instructor are authoritative.
